  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230ºC/ 210ºC (fan)/ gas 8, take your <strong>steaks</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature</p><p>Pat the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> with kitchen paper and cut the <strong>rind </strong>off the steaks, then using a sharp knife, score the rind on a diagonal, being careful not to cut all the way through</p><p>Add the <strong>scored rind </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1725272615184-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1725272615184-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1725272615184-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1725272615184-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1725272615184-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15-22 min or until the pork rind is golden and crispy, then set aside until cooled – this is your <strong>crackling</strong></p><p>Cover the<strong> steaks</strong> in<strong> cling film</strong> and bash them with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until evenly flattened to approx. 1cm in thickness</p><p>Combine 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and your <strong>dried sage</strong> on a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then drizzle the <strong>flattened steaks</strong> with a little <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>press them into the <strong>seasoned flour</strong> until well coated – this is your<strong> coated pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1725272618404-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1725272618404-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1725272618404-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1725272618404-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1725272618404-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender and once cooked, drain and return them to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1725272621711-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1725272621711-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1725272621711-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1725272621711-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1725272621711-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated pork</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>pork scaloppines</strong></p><p>Once cooked through, transfer the <strong>pork scaloppines </strong>to a plate to rest and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1725272625084-x200.jpg",
